I did not use the 'mutation catalyst' or attempt any combinations based on the prior warning about low scores from combining. You might try combining or the mutation catalyst if you want to experiment beyond these consistent but moderate scores.

message: The 'growth serum' tool is your best friend for guaranteed points. Use it on every ingredient you have. You'll find that large creatures (like lion, giraffe, shark) turn into 'grown' versions worth 15 points. Medium creatures (octopus, snake, crab, zebra, kangaroo, squid) become 'grown' and are worth 10 points. Small creatures (butterfly, pufferfish, bird) become 'grown' and are worth 5 points. Prioritize using the growth serum on large creatures first to maximize your score quickly, then medium, then small. After applying it to all ingredients, simply submit. I did not experiment with the 'mutation catalyst' or combining items, as the 'growth serum' strategy consistently yielded scores between 10-15 points per round. If you want to aim higher, you might try exploring those options after securing a good baseline score.

message: The most consistent and reliable strategy I found was to use the 'growth serum' on every single initial ingredient you start with, and then immediately submit. Do not combine items or use the mutation catalyst. Growth serum consistently increased item values: large items to 15, medium items to 10, and small items to 5. Your score will be the value of the highest item, so always aim to get at least one large item to 15. This strategy consistently yields a score of 15 each round without any risk of decreasing your score. The previous player's advice about 'growth serum only once on each and just submit' was very accurate.
